Immediate benefit from the merger,

        LablGTK beta2 and LablGL 0.93

are now available for Objective Caml 2.99 on Unix/X11.

They are respectively interfaces to GTK+ (version 1.2.x)
and OpenGL/Mesa.

Due to technical problems, the web page is not available currently.
You can find these two libraries on ftp servers:

  ftp://ftp.inria.fr/lang/caml-light/bazar-ocaml/lablgtk-b2.tar.gz
  ftp://ftp.inria.fr/lang/caml-light/bazar-ocaml/lablgl-0.93.tar.gz
or
  ftp://ftp.kurims.kyoto-u.ac.jp/pub/lang/olabl/lablgtk-b2.tar.gz
  ftp://ftp.kurims.kyoto-u.ac.jp/pub/lang/olabl/lablgl-0.93.tar.gz

Changes for LablGTK:

* added a GUI for B. Pierce and T. Jim's unison file synchronizer.

* changes in many functions due to the new optionals rule.

* constructors are no longer classes, they are function
  with the same name as the widget wrapper class.

Changes for LablGL:

* togl.cmo is not included in lablgl.cma, to allow use with lablGTK
  instead of labltk.

* changes in optionals

------------------------------------------------------
Jacques Garrigue, visiting INRIA from Kyoto University
